// Alternative methods:
// Alt + Shift + Tab - Switch in reverse order
// Win + Tab - Open Task View (Windows 10/11)
// Ctrl + Alt + Tab - Keep Task Switcher open

// Alternative methods:
// Ctrl + Shift + Tab - Switch tabs in reverse
// Ctrl + 1,2,3... - Jump to specific tab number
// Ctrl + W - Close current tab
// Ctrl + T - Open new tab

// Alternative methods:
// Win + M - Minimize all windows (no restore)
// Win + Shift + M - Restore minimized windows
// Right-click taskbar → Show desktop
// Win + Home - Minimize all except active window

// Alternative methods:
// Right-click Start button → File Explorer
// Click File Explorer icon in taskbar
// Win + R → explorer → Enter
// Ctrl + Shift + N - New folder in current location

// Additional line navigation:
// Ctrl + Home - Move to beginning of document
// Ctrl + End - Move to end of document
// Shift + Home/End - Select to beginning/end of line
// Ctrl + Shift + Home/End - Select to beginning/end of document

// Additional clipboard shortcuts:
// Ctrl + Shift + V - Paste without formatting
// Ctrl + A - Select all
// Ctrl + Z - Undo
// Ctrl + Y - Redo
// Win + V - Open clipboard history (Windows 10/11)

// Alternative redo shortcuts:
// Ctrl + Shift + Z - Redo (in some applications)
// F4 - Repeat last action
// Ctrl + R - Refresh/Reload
// Ctrl + F5 - Hard refresh (browser)

// Additional deletion shortcuts:
// Backspace - Delete character to the left
// Delete - Delete character to the right
// Shift + Delete - Delete selected item permanently
// Ctrl + Shift + Delete - Open disk cleanup

// Additional VS Code shortcuts:
// Ctrl + P - Quick Open (files)
// Ctrl + Shift + N - New window
// Ctrl + ` - Toggle terminal
// Ctrl + B - Toggle sidebar
// Ctrl + Shift + E - Focus explorer

